nodes.proof:
Assume that such a map exists. If $n=0$ there is nothing to prove, so we assume that $n\ge 1$. In this case, we cannot have $m=0$, because a group of exponential growth cannot regularly embed into a polynomial growth group. Hence $m\ge 1$ as well. Now, by Theorem~\ref{th:profilemonotonuous} and Proposition~\ref{prop:profileofshufnofpolynomialgrowthgroups}, one has 
\begin{equation}\label{eq:ComparisonProfile2}
